AB  - This chapter focuses on open floating sea cages, which are those most used for intensive aquaculture. The description and calculation of waves and wave forces are quite difficult, and the chapter gives only a brief survey. Waves, current and wind all transfer energy to the sea cage farm; a part of this energy will only pass through the farm, but a part will be taken up in the sea cages. The difference between the incoming energy and the energy on the other side of the farm determines the energy that the farm construction and mooring system have to take up. There is a lot to consider when calculating the current forces on sea cages, and usually specially designed computer programs are used for this purpose. A simple set of equations and diagrams have been developed for calculation of the current forces on rigid sea cages.
